Sentencas: Ni/Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta,5 (Ni/GDC) and La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3-delta/Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (LSCF/GDC) porous thin-film electrodes with thicknesses between 120 and 500 nm were synthesized through templated sol-gel chemistry coupled with the dip-coating process and heat treatment.
Titulo: Discussion on a Percolating Conducting Network of a Composite Thin-Film Electrode (≤1 μm) for Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: The thin films consist of two interpenetrated networks made of pores and inorganic materials.
Titulo: Discussion on a Percolating Conducting Network of a Composite Thin-Film Electrode (≤1 μm) for Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: The porous structure was composed of multi-scale pores with dimensions ranging from macro- to nanosize and with an oriented columnar structure.
Titulo: Discussion on a Percolating Conducting Network of a Composite Thin-Film Electrode (≤1 μm) for Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: The dimension of the percolation network is discussed as a function of the chemical nature of the percolating components and the particle/thickness ratio.
Titulo: Discussion on a Percolating Conducting Network of a Composite Thin-Film Electrode (≤1 μm) for Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: A three-dimensional percolation network is achieved in the LSCF/GDC composite, while a two-dimensional percolation network is observed for the Ni/GDC composite.
Titulo: Discussion on a Percolating Conducting Network of a Composite Thin-Film Electrode (≤1 μm) for Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: This difference is related to the microstructure of the composite thin film.
Titulo: Discussion on a Percolating Conducting Network of a Composite Thin-Film Electrode (≤1 μm) for Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Application

Sentencas: An anisotropic columnar structure is observed for Ni/GDC, while an isotropic structure is achieved for LSCF/GDC.
Titulo: Discussion on a Percolating Conducting Network of a Composite Thin-Film Electrode (≤1 μm) for Micro-Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Application
